One of the most underrated glute exercises‼️‼️

BULGARIAN SPLIT SQUATS (glute focus)
**have your legs positioned in a longer stride and torso leaning forward. This puts your glutes in a stretched position. Focus on pushing through your front heel. You can use a bench, a barbell with a pad (my preferred method) or whatever is available. Recently I’ve been increasing my weight and using a bench for stability has been key!

I’m obsessed with this exercise!! (All in one: Shoulders, Core, Back)
KB Gorilla Rows: Keep your core firm and ensure your lower back is not round. Keep one kettlebell in your hand and row the other weight back towards your hip. Keep same tone through your abdominals as you pull the kettlebells into your body to ensure you don’t arch excessively through your spine.
